info.title: Create a Connection
info.description: Creates a new connection within a specified group in your Fivetran account. Runs setup tests and returns testing results.

operation.description: Creates a new connection within a specified group in your Fivetran account. Runs setup tests and returns testing results.

id.description: The unique identifier for the connection within the Fivetran system

service.description: The connector name within the Fivetran system

schema.description: The name used both as the connection's name within the Fivetran system and as the source schema's name within your destination

paused.description: Specifies whether the connection is paused

daily_sync_time.description: The connection daily sync start time that we return only when the sync frequency is set to 1440 (which means 24 hours) and the daily_sync_time parameter was set using the Create a Connection or Update a Connection request

succeeded_at.description: The timestamp of the time the connection sync succeeded last time

sync_frequency.description: The connection sync frequency in minutes

group_id.description: The unique identifier for the group within the Fivetran system

connected_by.description: The unique identifier of the user who has created the connection in your account

setup_tests.description: Setup tests results for this connection

source_sync_details.description: The additional information about the connection's state. The format of this parameter is specific for each connection type

service_version.description: The connector version within the Fivetran system

created_at.description: The timestamp of the time the connection was created in your account

failed_at.description: The timestamp of the time the connection sync failed last time

private_link_id.description: The unique identifier for the self-served private link that is used by the connection

proxy_agent_id.description: The unique identifier for the proxy agent within the Fivetran system

pause_after_trial.description: Specifies whether the connection should be paused after the free trial period has ended

data_delay_threshold.description: Custom sync delay notification threshold in minutes. The default value is 0. This parameter is only used when data_delay_sensitivity set to CUSTOM.

data_delay_sensitivity.description: The level of data delay notification threshold. Possible values: LOW, NORMAL, HIGH, CUSTOM, SYNC_FREQUENCY. The default value NORMAL. CUSTOM is only available for customers using the [Enterprise plan](https://fivetran.com/docs/getting-started/pricing#fivetranplans) or above.

schedule_type.description: The connection schedule configuration type. Supported values: auto, manual

hybrid_deployment_agent_id.description: The unique identifier for the hybrid deployment agent within the Fivetran system. If not specified, the agent ID from the destination will be used

tasks.description: The collection of tasks for the connection

warnings.description: The collection of warnings for the connection

schema_status.description: Schema status. Returned only for connectors that support [Universal Column Masking flow](https://fivetran.com/docs/rest-api/tutorials/schema-status).

update_state.description:
The current data update state of the connection. The available values are:
- on_schedule - the sync is running smoothly, no delays
- delayed - the data is delayed for a longer time than expected for the update.

setup_state.description:
The current setup state of the connection. The available values are:
- incomplete - the setup config is incomplete, the setup tests never succeeded
- connected - the connection is properly set up
- broken - the connection setup config is broken.

sync_state.description:
The current sync state of the connection. The available values are:
- scheduled - the sync is waiting to be run
- syncing - the sync is currently running
- paused - the sync is currently paused
- rescheduled - the sync is waiting until more API calls are available in the source service.

is_historical_sync.description: The boolean specifying whether the connection should be triggered to re-sync all historical data. If you set this parameter to TRUE, the next scheduled sync will be historical. If the value is FALSE or not specified, the connection will not re-sync historical data. NOTE: When the value is TRUE, only the next scheduled sync will be historical, all subsequent ones will be incremental. This parameter is set to FALSE once the historical sync is completed.

rescheduled_for.description: The scheduled time for the next sync when sync_state is rescheduled. If schedule_type is manual, then the connection expects triggering the event at the designated time through the [Sync Connection Data](https://fivetran.com/docs/rest-api/api-reference/connections/sync-connection) endpoint.

redirect_uri.description: The URI on your site we redirect the end user to after successful setup. The URI must start with the `https` or `http` prefix.

hide_setup_guide.description: An optional parameter that lets you hide the embedded setup guide in the Connect Card.

virtual_warehouse.description: Snowflake's virtual warehouse used in the connection

uri.description: The Connect Card URI for the user interface

group_id.description: The unique identifier for the group within the Fivetran system

service.description: The connector name within the Fivetran system

trust_certificates.description: Specifies whether we should trust the certificate automatically. The default value is FALSE. If a certificate is not trusted automatically, it has to be approved with [Certificates Management API Approve a destination certificate](https://fivetran.com/docs/rest-api/certificates#approveadestinationcertificate).

trust_fingerprints.description: Specifies whether we should trust the SSH fingerprint automatically. The default value is FALSE. If a fingerprint is not trusted automatically, it has to be approved with [Certificates Management API Approve a destination fingerprint](https://fivetran.com/docs/rest-api/certificates#approveadestinationfingerprint).

run_setup_tests.description: Specifies whether the setup tests should be run automatically. The default value is TRUE.

paused.description: Specifies whether the connection is paused

pause_after_trial.description: Specifies whether the connection should be paused after the free trial period has ended

sync_frequency.description: The connection sync frequency in minutes

data_delay_sensitivity.description: The level of data delay notification threshold. Possible values: LOW, NORMAL, HIGH, CUSTOM, SYNC_FREQUENCY. The default value NORMAL. CUSTOM is only available for customers using the [Enterprise plan](https://fivetran.com/docs/getting-started/pricing#fivetranplans) or above.

data_delay_threshold.description: Custom sync delay notification threshold in minutes. The default value is 0. This parameter is only used when data_delay_sensitivity set to CUSTOM.

daily_sync_time.description: The optional parameter that defines the sync start time when the sync frequency is already set or being set by the current request to 1440. It can be specified in one hour increments starting from 00:00 to 23:00. If not specified, we will use [the baseline sync start time](https://fivetran.com/docs/getting-started/syncoverview#syncfrequencyandscheduling). This parameter has no effect on the [0 to 60 minutes offset](https://fivetran.com/docs/getting-started/syncoverview#syncstarttimesandoffsets) used to determine the actual sync start time

schedule_type.description: The connection schedule configuration type. Supported values: auto, manual

proxy_agent_id.description: The unique identifier for the proxy agent within the Fivetran system

private_link_id.description: The unique identifier for the self-served private link that is used by the connection

hybrid_deployment_agent_id.description: The unique identifier for the hybrid deployment agent within the Fivetran system. If not specified, the agent ID from the destination will be used

destination_schema_names.description:
Defines how you want the schema names to appear in your destination.
The available values are:
- FIVETRAN_NAMING - Use Fivetran naming conventions to simplify and standardize the schema, table and column names in the destination.
- SOURCE_NAMING - Preserve source schema table and column names in the destination.
You can modify your selection only before the initial sync. Learn more in [our documentation](https://fivetran.com/docs/core-concepts#namingconventions)
